Only a moron goes on holiday to Durban in February – the one month in the year when the council has to mop up puddles of melted people at the end of each day. I, apparently, am nothing if not a moron. In my defence, this was to be a working holiday of sorts. Contrast being one of life’s more piquant spices, pleasure is generally best combined with a dash of suffering. So I would use the opportunity to visit my 82-year-old father. That would take care of the suffering portion. Old people are a pain. If you are old...